cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order logic and its fragments. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper gives a characterization of languages recognized by automata definable in fragments of first-order logic. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with sets and their properties. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) could be relevant as the paper discusses the analysis of algorithms on infinite structures. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the foundations of mathematics and their relation to practical applications.
